			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1305175">
									

<p>In my mind, that would be like asking if seeing 096 in a different color would help. So, if that were the case, tinted glasses could give you protection from 096. Since blurring could be argued to change the color of any given point on 096, bad vision, hot pavement, or even <em>squinting</em> could stop 096.</p>
<p>In other words, I imagine that the fact that it's 096's face would be enough to trigger it. Altering the image of 096 wouldn't be enough to stop it; you would need to block it entirely (as they did in the picture provided).</p>

