														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1544100">
									

<p>Brilliant incident log, but one thing kind of bugs me: SCRAMBLE gear would not have worked at all even if the scrambling effect had been instantaneous. If a picture containing four pixels could be recognized by 096's supernatural ability, wouldn't a scrambled image be just as recognizable, since it's basically the same thing? Now, knowing that the four-pixel picture worked, the scientists working on SCRAMBLE would know why it didn't work. So the &quot;split second before scrambling&quot; explanation of why SCRAMBLE didn't work makes no sense. It wouldn't work even if that split second wasn't there, and the scientists should have realized that.</p>
<p>Other than that very minor gripe, very good incident report.</p>

							</div>

								
					
