			<div class="content" id="post-content-4542847">
									

<p>It doesn't make any sense and he shouldn't have been able to. My headcanon excludes it altogether. An AWACS has a cruising altitude of 30,000 feet, there's no way 096 could magically get up there. Yes he went to the bottom of the ocean, but that makes sense. The only reason we can't go to the bottom of the ocean is because the pressure would kill us or we would drown. 096 is indestructible so this obviously isn't an issue for him, he can just swim down. That isn't the case with freaking <em>air</em>. You can't just start flying by waving your arms around.</p>

